name: Sandeep Mall
text:
To get to a certain goal, u need to build certain skills. To build these skills, u need to do certain practices regularly. Break these practices to manageable and consistent small steps. 
Ask for help. That’s the easiest and fastest way to reach your goals. Keep a growth mindset

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Like if you want to run a marathon in 10 months- u may need to spend an hour to your training 5 days a week. Make an appointment with yourself for this daily action 
Go from goals to skills to practise.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Write your goal - can be anything from running a marathon to financial to own a house to write a book. 
Write down the skills needed to reach that goal - the ability or capacity to achieve that goal. 
Give a timeline to your goal
Breakdown your goals to smaller daily goals

text:
Slow Drive. U rarely reach anywhere earlier driving fast. And ur cars life and mileage will be much better. 
Slow breathe. Most of us over breathe 12-20 breathe a minute. Slow it down to 6-8 a minute 
Slow life is the mantra for healthy happy and satisfied life.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Slow down you attention. Our attention is pulled in hundreds of direction. 
Slow down your work. Working at a slower pace will be more productive though it sounds contradictory. 
Slow Eat. Instead of gobbling your food, chew it and relish. And keep away TV or phone or newspaper.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Do u rush from one place to another? Is you schedule packed with errands and tasks? Do u have a hectic life every waking moment? Slow down. Learn to move at a slower pace and u will be happier, productive and more effective.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Consistency is the key. 2 day schedule is better than 4 if u r consistently missing workouts. If your exercises are based on movement patterns you will get fantastic results. Look what’s best for you. But be consistent and don’t miss strength training

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Upper/lower split if for people who can train 4 x per week. Mostly experienced gym goers. They want to maximise strength and muscle gains. Also depends on your present schedule. If you have busy days do 2-3 days full body, if u have light schedule ramp up to UB/LB split

name: Sandeep Mall
text: There are two ways to split your weight training - Full body and Upper/Lower split. Full body is for most people. They can commit to weight training 2-3 times a week. Goal is modest strength and muscle building

text: @anshu_seeds @yamunajiye I am a fighter for environment. And obviously I will never give up on behaviour change. But let’s be honest & practical. text: Repeat 8-10 times during your activity. You may use a pulse oximeter while doing this and don’t let oxygen level go below 80. Or if u feel dizzy stop.This is a very important tool to increase your heart rate recovery, resting heart rate, maximum aerobic fitness. #newIndiaFitIndia

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Warm up properly for 10 mins or so during your walking, running or cycling activity. Always do nasal breathing. Gently exhale and pinch ur nose. Hold it until u feel a strong hunger for air. Release your nose and minimise your breathe by taking short breathes. https://t.co/c8W43WYaul

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Calculate your maximum aerobic HR. As per him if u r between 16-65, 180- your age is your Max Aerobic heart rate. Calculate that and do most of your workouts in that. Keep testing your improvements in that HR. I have been experimenting with this for sometime

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Fitness and health are two separate things. Aerobic strength is what we need to work on for our better health. Fat burning happens in aerobic stage. Most of the training should be in aerobic stage. And Dr Phil Maffetone has devised as simple formula for this

name: Sandeep Mall
text: No pain, no gain maybe the most misused phrase ever.There is no fun to be in pain. No pain no gain may make you fit but unhealthy.The best way to get healthy is by burning fat. Our exercise and movement should be such that we use fat for fuel. Find ways to slow the ageing process

name: Sandeep Mall
text: 6. Be liberal with delete key. Too often we feel like we need to reply to every email or message. you cant reply to every thing. Just choose the important one and delete.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
4. Use a good Junk filter. Most of the emails these days are junk. Gmail definitely does a great job in this.
5. Turn off Email or other messaging notifications. They do create a disturbance

name: Sandeep Mall
text: 3. Limit time on Email. I check my mails twice a day. First thing in the morning ( not advisable though) but that's my half an hour working time. I respond all emails or write to my team and customers if I need any info. Second time I check post lunch.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
2. Combine multiple accounts to forward to one account. SO u don't have to spend time checking multiple accounts. 
What I do is forward all mails related to my Most Important tasks in hand to one email id. Rest goes to one. The fewer inboxes u have better

name: Sandeep Mall
text: 1. Limit your inboxes The more places you have to check messages, the harder it becomes. It takes away your precious time and concentration. Evaluate each to see if it gives value. If something is not giving value eliminate them.

text:
The one goal system will keep you focused on achieving your goal, moving closer to it each day. It will allow you to focus all your energy on completing this goal. Simplifying your task can be the most important step you take. 

So what’s your goal by the end 2021.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I will further break it down to daily goals - which maybe waking up early and devoting an hour to running or strength training. And good hydration and 8 hours of sleep

name: Sandeep Mall
text: ..than a larger year long goal might be. I will then break them into weekly goals that will take me closer to my sub goal. Say I have to run 40 hours a week. One interval run, one long run, one Fartlek, one strength training, couple of foam rolling sessions

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Break it down to sub goals. Say my goal is to run a full marathon in Jan 2022. For that I will break it down to sub goals of next 1-2 months which maybe by May,I will do 18 kms long run .The reason for this is to create shorter goals that are more immediately achievable..

name: Sandeep Mall
text: the stronger your desire, the more likely you are going to stick with it until the goal is finished. Also choose a goal that will finish in 6-12 months. Anything longer than that, you will have problem maintaining focus. Anything less may not be worth your focus.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
The most effective way to get success with your goals is to focus on one goal at a time. 
Make a list of goals you have in mind. It can be 10-20 or even more. Then choose one goal that you really want to accomplish -

name: Sandeep Mall
text: It’s easy to set goals but extremely difficult to achieve them if they are goals worth achieving. Tackling a goal takes energy, focus and motivation- three things that are in limited supply in any person. #LunchtimeTweet

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
The happiest moment was when I cleared all debt and released my home from mortgage. Saved a substantial emergency fund for me and my family. Tips that will help :
1. Start small. Dont try to do too many things at a time
2. Simplify. Declutter
3. Create habits

name: Sandeep Mall
text: The newspaper & TV time came to zero. I cut off completely from things that didn’t matter to me. Books &blogs were limited to self help & health. Completely cut down multi tasking. The concept of one goal at a time and putting all my energy into it worked wonderfully well for me.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I started decluttering lot of activities and things. One thing at a time. I poured my energy into the one thing . First was making more time.  Created time by buying time. Hiring the best people that I could afford to do things I was doing.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: And then the car crash happened which forced me to get things order. To Simplify. To make positive changes.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I was over my head in debt.I wasn’t exercising and I was a smoker. My life was complicated and I didn’t have time for anything that I loved. And though I was aware of it but had no time to even plan a way out.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Only a few years back, I had a work schedule that rarely allowed me to see my family and had me stressed to maximum. I rarely had time for holidays. In fact I just had very few holidays with my boys. I was over weight and unhealthy eating fried and fatty.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: You don't need to run marathons to have a great health span. Running is a strenuous workout and should only be started when ready for it, not randomly. Having said that, if you can master it, there is nothing like running. Its more than meditation.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Wearing cushioned shoes is not soft landing. That actually does more harm. You may land 2-3000 times running a km and based on your weight imagine the impact its putting on your feet. If not done right, you may suffer knee issues.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Running is a great activity, if done right. While running, landing incurs a force that is 2.5 to 3 times body weight. At the knee, this force can be 7 times body weight. Ur landing has to be soft. Your form has to be right. And build some strength before starting to run

text: Each one is right from their perspective - this line is to be underlined in our minds. It helps us radiate respect, put our point across calmly, and accept differences with stability. #Brahmakumaris

name: Sandeep Mall
text: There’s more power in being humble than to argue. Otherwise it becomes a power game of us being right rather than our opinion being right. Arguments arise out of ego and block productive communication

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Also, do lengthy arguments feel worthwhile? Being heard is important. But healthy discussions need us to pause, process the situation, create a response and then speak. We also need to listen to their opinion without internally concluding they are wrong.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: But if we choose to emotionally withdraw, remain stable and then speak, the dialogue moves towards harmony despite our differences. What is your threshold for calm interactions during a verbal exchange? Does your temperament flare and you argue to prove your point?

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Differences of opinions arise in everyday interactions, as the sanskars and perspectives we all carry differ. At such times if we are egoistic to prove our point and criticize the other person, the discussion turns into an argument.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Ensure you increase strength more than muscle mass. The Neuro muscular connections need to be optimised. Functional strength needs to be good. You love walking, running or yoga. That’s great. But don’t avoid strength training. Don’t try to abuse benefits of ST. U will need it

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Start young. I started at 46. Gaining muscle mass becomes damn difficult at that age. You start to lose muscle around 30. I had already lost huge strength in two decades. You should not be terrified of gym or lifting weights, u should be terrified of bed rest.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: A Norwegian study (https://t.co/drOb7uJ0iF) shows one week of bed rest resulted in 1.4 kg lean tissue loss and Vo2 decline by 6.4 in 23 year olds. 70 year olds lost 2.6 kgs muscle. You just can’t afford to get injured. And a good strength will help you prevent that.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: If u train really hard, you might be able to reduce it to certain extent, and if u really go crazy like me, u might be able to go flat. Once u get into 70s, the decline gets steeper. And even a weeks bed rest can be disaster even in healthy young people forget oldies

name: Sandeep Mall
text: a chair or commode by yourself. And I can’t over emphasise that you need to do strength training for a healthy old age. From a health perspective you need to put some muscle mass - male or female. If you do nothing you are going to lose ‘x’ pound of muscles every decade

text: When bedtime approaches, be careful with your screens. Stuff on your phone or tablet can stir you up in equally positive and negative ways, but no matter, they block your sense that it’s time to sleep. So be mindful with your screens in the evening

name: Sandeep Mall
text: When you’re outside in daylight, you regulate your body’s biological clock, and this can make it easier to sleep at night. The earlier you expose yourself, preferably half an hour in a stretch, the more likely you are to feel sleepy when evening comes.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Coffee is a treat for body and mind, but part of this treat is that it fires you up. When bedtime approaches, you want the opposite. Avoid coffee after 2 PM

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Alcohol maybe puts you to sleep faster, but it causes unrest. Whatever sleep you’re getting, it’s not as restorative. You’ll feel weary, even if you clocked your hours. If u still have to drink, don’t drink three or four hours before bedtime.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
What we do when we’re awake, influences the quality of our sleep at night. It’s about you taking control over your situation. You’re in charge of your sleep. #gettingfitterwithsandeep @FitIndiaOff

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Too often we see people rushing to the main workout without preparation. This is going to lead to bad soreness or injury and limiting range of motion. And I end my workout with 5-7 minutes of breathing exercise to release all the stress and calm the body and heart. @FitIndiaOff

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Eg-Squat is going to be my primary workout on my lower body day.I start with foam rolling quads, calves and hamstring. Next will do dynamic stretches to open up hips, quad, hamstring and ankle. Will do glute bridges to power them up for squat. Few warmup sets and then 5 main sets

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Then do few light weight sets before hitting the primary workout.  It should prime your body for a productive workout - one that maximises results and minimises risk of injury. The idea is to unlock mobility, improve quality of movement, ignite more powerful muscle contractions

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Start with foam rolling the body part u r going to workout that day. Prepare the soft tissues. Than do dynamic stretching to support the exercises. Most people do a poor job of warming up effectively. An effective warm up should be specific to the primary exercise u have planned

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Preparing for a workout is very important to avoid any sort of soreness , pain or injury. Going to gym or a running track and not doing enough warmup is a sure short invitation for some injury. Or if u just hop on to a tread mill for 10 mins to warm up it’s not helping u.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Summing up the benefits of HIIT
1.Builds work capacity…so you can handle training longer, harder and more frequently.
2.Enhances the speed at which you can recovery.
3.A potent fat-loss tool.
4.A great method to improve all-round fitness and cardiovascualr health. @FitIndiaOff

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I don’t time my rest period. It’s till the HR comes down to normal. As u will see 4th round onwards the rest time is more as Its taking time for it to get normal. If I start timed for every round I will not be able give my best at the high intensity time & thus have less benefit https://t.co/FeAM6tJOsG

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I either go sprinting outdoors or do rowing indoors. A typical workout will be 10 mins warmup followed by 2 mins rowing at max effort (170 bpm HR) and rest till HR comes back to near normal. Repeat 6 rounds. Cool down 10 mins. Doing more will hamper ur recovery for next day.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: My problem with body weight group classes is most(90% of the people ) do the form wrong. There is a time bound rush. And the trainer has so many people to monitor. U will end up doing more harm to yourself. HIIT can be super effective and but can just as easily be destructive

name: Sandeep Mall
text: VSome of the exercise that can help u do this is Sprinting, Cycling, Rowing. And remember not to do it more than a week. Most of the training should be low intensity. The worlds best athletes also do 15-20% of their training in high intensity.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: To qualify for HIIT you need to do 10 minutes of true ‘red zone’ VO2 Max intensity work. The total workout maybe 20-30 mins which includes rest in between. Bodyweight exercises, no matter how out of breath they may leave you will not hit this intensity of effort. Not even close.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: High intensity means “above 90% VO2 max.” VO2 max is the maximum volume of oxygen that your body can use. It’s often measured in mL/kg/min and represents an exercise intensity that taps out your aerobic metabolism. And if u have done a VO2 max test u will know how hard it is.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: See so many people doing body weight exercises in the name of HIIT. Let me explain what’s HIIT so that you can utilise to power of such a wonderful fitness tool. HIIT is “repeated bouts of high intensity work interspersed with periods of passive or active rest.” https://t.co/6bkmzfRjPZ

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Babuji used to say - जो देता है सो पाता है। And it’s always true in the bigger picture. As an entrepreneur it’s your only role in your organisation is to make a team or givers. And if u are in a job honestly try to be a giver. The road may look long but it will lead to success.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Givers are rare breed in a workplace. Givers are other focused paying more attention to what others need from them. They help others so that the organisation benefits more. They share their time, energy, skills, ideas. In the short term this looks losing strategy.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Their are always two types of people in a workplace - Takers and givers. Takers put their own interest ahead of others. They believe world is dog eat dog place. They self promote and take credit for their efforts. In the short term it looks they are winners. Me first

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Our success depends heavily on how we approach our interactions with other people. Every time we interact with another person at work, we have a choice to make: do we try to claim as much value as we can, or contribute value without worrying about what we receive in return?

text: In order to keep you stable while you do these single-limbed movements, your core has to go on a overdrive. When you're first getting started with unilateral training, let your weaker side determine the weight you use. Also start with your weak side first. @FitIndiaOff

name: Sandeep Mall
text: The stronger side will do slightly more than fifty percent of the work.This can prevent the weaker side from catching up, strength wise.The stronger muscle will be prone to injury because of over use.There's another important benefit of unilateral training: Improved core strength

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Do u do unilateral exercises ? Everyone has a dominant (stronger) and non-dominant (slightly less strong) side of the body. While doing bilateral workouts, the stronger side can overcompensate for the other, further widening the strength gap between the two sides. https://t.co/jy1yrt6uYt

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Do 30-60 minutes of aerobic exercises, which can be cycling,
Walking, yoga, strength training, swimming.These exercises don’t tax your heart as much as other high intensity exercises do. For most of us we need to choose our goal and shift gears at the right time

name: Sandeep Mall
text: So what are the best exercises for a good longevity- the Copenhagen City Herat study says. - Tennis , Badminton and soccer has the longest longevity benefits followed by cycling, swimming, calisthenics. Playing a sport is best for your longevity

name: Sandeep Mall
text: From your health perspective it’s fine to run one or two marathons for the sake of accomplishment but not as a regular habit. Until and unless u have a HR like that of @IamShajanSamuel . Even Micah True, the central character of Born to run - died due to cardiac failure

name: Sandeep Mall
text: At some point in your exercise routine u need to choose when to shift exercise from being an athletic performance to longevity. It’s like a formula one car. It can not last 50000 kms vs the cars we drive which lasts 500000 kms because driven at 70 kms or so per hour

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Running is not for everyone. It’s a very high intensity exercises. Once a few weeks it is ok to hit your heart rate to 90% of your MHR if longevity and good cardio vascular health is your goal. Specially after the age of 40 this stress will do u more harm than good.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: .. and increases with an increasing amount of exercise.(Don’t tell me u r so busy and stupid, that you can’t take out 15 minutes for yourself).  But like any drug, the dose must be appropriate. At higher doses some of the benefit is lost

name: Sandeep Mall
text: If exercising was a drug, it would be the best drug we have for preventing heart disease, dementia, osteoporosis, depression, diabetes and obesity. For decrease of serious cardio vascular disease, benefit of exercise start at just 15 minutes of brisk walking per day..

text: I had a great physician who made me understand my body. He advised me to check Uric acid level. As per him it makes no sense to try to medically correct hypertension if uric acid is above 5. I had 7.9. First he worked on reducing my uric acid.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Always check BP after ten minutes of rest. Not like going to a clinic and immediately checking. I prefer at home. For two weeks I will make a noting and then make an average. If it is above 130-80- I call my doctor. Kidney is the most sensitive organ to hypertension

text: Actions build on actions. Success builds on success. Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed at the things that you didn’t do than by the ones you did do. Life is too short to pile up I could, I should, I would. Success is an inside job.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: ..possible simplifies your thinking and crystallises what you must do. No matter how big your goal is, when you know where you are going and work backwards to what you need to do to get there, you will always reach there.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Apply this approach to anything you want to achieve - whether it is health or calmness or relationships or career or anything that matters to you. Take one step at a time towards your goal. Extraordinary results require you to go small. Getting your focus as small as ..

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Write down your current income. Multiply it by any number you want it to be - 2x,5x 10x or whatever. Then ask yourself will my current actions take me to these numbers in next 5 years. Replan your actions accordingly. Get a mentor if you don’t know the path.

text: In fact, bending the knees half way to about 90 degrees, with thighs parallel to the ground can activate more muscles than any other squat position. Start squatting even if you are able to do quarter squat and gradually go deep as muscles grow strong.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: But as adults, after sitting in chairs too much and losing strength, our muscles may no longer be able to obtain, or maintain, the natural full squat. Not able to squat is going to severely effect health and fitness. If u r unable to squat full, don’t try and risk injury.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Along with standing, walking and lying down, humans have always used squatting for rest, play and work. We learn it as toddlers, when we were perfectly comfortable and stable in a full squat with only feet flat on the ground and butt resting on calves.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Muscles do more than move us-they are also necessary for structural support,optimal blood &lymph circulation,immune function,fat-burning &hormone production. Low muscle strength and mass affects other aspects of health and fitness - and is a significant predictor of mortality.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Don’t add repetitions as u get stronger. This will reduce the effectiveness of the workout. Instead as u become stronger add more weights. Don’t miss strength training. The loss of muscle mass &bone strength is reality with age. Decline starts to be visible from mid and late 30s

name: Sandeep Mall
text: For new to gym, I would not recommend this method but to simply experiment by starting light and increasing over weeks before you start noticing fatigue. No of reps will vary day to day depending how good ur recovery was. Don’t push it, keep it natural with what your body wants.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: If you are lifting weights regularly, it’s good to know your 1RM - theoretically max weight you can lift one time. And then lift 80% of that weight about 5-6 times before noticeable fatigue develops. Do 3-5 sets with good recovery time in between.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Muscle strength isn't really about the size of a muscle but the amount of muscle fibers employed during a strength activity. Your approach to training should be increase ability to contract more muscle power so that no excess fatigue or soreness and pain happens next day.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: The point of a workout is not to exhaust the body - but to strengthen the body, and not sacrifice health. When we get fooled into thinking that the point of a workout is to fatigue the body into soreness or pain, we weaken and risk damaging it, requiring longer recovery.

text: Or, they’re turned off about going to a gym and seeing all those muscular bodies and mirrors. Unfortunately, most don’t really know how easy it is to get stronger. Don’t be overwhelmed. Get a coach. Start training. Take care of urself.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Many people are reluctant, hesitant, confused, even discouraged from gaining back their body strength to feel — and be — healthy, fit, and physiologically younger again. They may feel there is no time in the day to add another workout to an already busy life.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: There is a simple remedy — stay strong! Even if we didn’t build as much strength when we were younger, it’s not too late to start as we can not only maintain what we have, but muscle strength can quickly improve with the right training.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Many believe substantial muscle and bone weakness is part of aging — but it’s actually part of unhealthy aging. Bones also can grow weaker from poor physical muscle activity. My 75 plus parents do strength training 4 days.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Most people feel older than they are, have aches and pains, and physical injuries. They can’t lift, carry or grip things like they used to, and frequently experience fatigue or have low stamina. Most have not only lost strength but muscle mass as well.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Muscle &bone weakness can cause or contribute to problems that range from simple or chronic injuries, physical disability or lower quality of life at any age,to frailty and loss of independence with aging. Muscle weakness is an important indicator of chronic disease and mortality

text: Our post workout breathing routine to calm the system. 4 seconds in - 7 hold and 8 seconds out. https://t.co/l99xMKna6i

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Maintain the same when strength training. Brace abs to keep spine stable. Breathe in strongly during eccentric phase to create maximal intra abdominal pressure. Breathe out sharply through pursed lips during concentric phase. Breathe right. Breathe strong.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Once u master this move to power breathing. Deep nose inhale into abdomen and sharp exhale through pursed lips. This will create more activation and is a preferred method of breathing doing core exercises. This will progress your core strength.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: To practice get into plank position. Do normal diaphragmatic breathing. The abdomen won’t rise as it does with normal diaphragmatic breathing but you will feel pressure building up - infra abdominal pressure.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Breathing during core workout - Fundamentally u should be doing diaphragmatic breathing - in through nose deep and breathe out through nose or mouth. It will take some practise to breathe with braced abs this way. Shallow breathe into chest or breathe holding is inefficient

text: Resistance is the enemy within. Decision to begin now is one thought away. Let’s be determined and discipline our mind. Remind yourselves - I am committed to my tasks, my happiness and my health. I don’t delay anything. I take action now. Wake up and shine.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: We usually postpone important matters - by not paying bills or tax until the last date, not valuing a relationship until it breaks, not switching to a healthy diet until we fall ill, not giving up addictions until they severely affect us, not exercising until doctor insists…

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Is there a perfect time that you wait for, to change anything about you, or to complete a pending task? Do you habitually postpone them saying I will start on ... New year … my birthday ... weekend … next week … next month? Started this book last night. 3rd of 2021 https://t.co/RgJvbX0aUk

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
Some tips to recover fast 
1. Hydrate consistently. Make sure you drink water consistently through out the day 
2. Eating a well rounded diet tailored to your body has a major impact on your recovery. Eat the right kind of food for your body 
3. Understand the signs ur body...

name: Sandeep Mall

name: Sandeep Mall
text: To maximise oxygen delivery to the working muscle we need high concentration of Co2 in the blood. With mouth breathing, we over breathe and exhale too much Co2 which reduces oxygen delivery. Over time with my tolerance improving I incorporated it in my running. This can be a

name: Sandeep Mall
text: thereby maximising performance. Like most I also used to believe that breathing through mouth delivers more oxygen to lungs. This assumption is entirely wrong. As we all must have during oxygen checks with oximeter that blood is almost fully saturated (95-99%)

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I started it with my low intensity spinning sessions and found that my performance soared. I could endure more power output for significantly longer at my max aerobic fitness heart rate. What I learnt is that breathing through nose delivers more oxygen to the working muscles

name: Sandeep Mall
text: There was a time when I needed sweet with every meal. That’s no longer true. I think it’s not hard to eliminate pathological need of sugar for sweet things. You are best off if u can avoid everything sweet. But if not use substitute than sugar. And Jaggery is sugar.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: If u must drink a sweet beverage or food, you are better off using a substitute for sugar than sugar. Xylitol for eg looks and tastes like sugar but has fewer calories and doesn’t raise blood sugar. Or aspartame( Equal) or sucralose( Splenda).

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I believe once you eliminate sugar from your diet, you craving for sugar will actually vanish. I used to take my tea and coffee with sugar and last few years stopped it and now can’t even have one sip with sugar in them. It tastes yuck and leaves a bad taste in the mouth

name: Sandeep Mall
text: And it’s now not in just the obvious places like candies or sweets. It’s in salad dressings, sauces, healthy sports drinks, low fat healthy yoghurt & what not. It has sneaked into almost every packaged food. Real sugar is toxin. It’s probability as chronically harmful as tobacco.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: It’s now 8 days without sugar. When I say Sugar, I mean everything which masquerade as sugar from honey to gur. Once u realise how harmful sugar is u really would not like to go back to it Do u know our intake of sugar has gone up by 400% from 1970.

name: Sandeep Mall

name: Sandeep Mall

Morning workouts offer numerous benefits to your health and schedule that exercising at other times of the day cant provide. A closer look at the benefits

Some data points to monitor. 
1) Body fat percentage - Ideal for men -less than 18. For women - less than 26%. 
2. Waist /hip ration - Ideal for men .9 for women .85. 
3. Blood Pressure - between 120-80
4. Heart rate Your resting heart rate is a great data point for your health

name: Sandeep Mall

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Apps these days are so smart. These are the apps I use and data source for most is my iWatch. Most data output is automatic. I use the paid version of these apps as the analysis is very good. name: Sandeep Mall
text: It’s not always negative. Maybe u tried a new sleep pattern and it’s working. All feedback is not necessary going to be bad. I am a great data sucker. I plan my workouts diet and everything depending on how my body is behaving. I make tons of notes and it hardly takes 2 mins

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Quantitative data like weight, body fat percentage, blood pressure , pulse etc helps u reorganise and correct. Qualitative data is important. Thirst, exhaustion, hunger, exhilaration. Ur body gives regular signs. If u keep ignoring them it becomes too late to course correct.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Your regular blood test data gives you information on your vitamins and minerals. Helps u to know if u need to supplement. Is there anything going on in your body that you should be aware of? You get two types of data - Quantitative and qualitative

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Let go of perfection. Be better consistently every day. My focus on workout has always been on consistence progress. Always listen to your body. Data is key to understand your body. Always collect and review ur data

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Most of what I tweet is my personal health protocol. I have found happiness with my life again. I want everyone to enjoy this bliss for life. And this is doable. Not easy but worth it. I believe u can also approach your health goals. Join in. Let’s get fitter together

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Fitness is not about six abs. It’s about living a pain free disease free confident life. What’s the point of that body in which u may look good but live with pain. My approach to fitness has been holistic. Physical, mental, and eating right. There is no quick fix .

name: Sandeep Mall
text: My own health journey started after a life changing injury. I was unhappy and in pain. I had enough money and family around but I was at my rock bottom and it led to an internal reckoning. And then life changed. Once u begin to find joy with your body you can never go back.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: माँ बाप भाई बहन , दोस्त, customer( जिनके साथ एक पेग नहीं लो तो networking नहीं होती) कोई साथ नहीं देता । आपका दर्द आपकी सेहत उसकी तकलीफ़ सिर्फ़ आपकी है। Your body is the only place where u get to live.

name: Sandeep Mall

name: Sandeep Mall
text: With Zone 2 Exercise done properly you would see improving fat Oxidation, improving lactate clearance & therefore improved mitochondrial function. You will seriously see the fat going down. Is it not your main goal of exercising and healthy life. That’s my zones of last 12 weeks https://t.co/frr7qReRiU

name: Sandeep Mall
text: When to do. Best is in morning. In Fasted state. U would want your insulin levels to be as low as possible because Insulin impairs lipolysis. In fasted state you will be oxidising more fat sooner in the workout as you will not take much time to shift from glucose as fuel to fat.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: How much to do for max results. Each session should be 45 minutes minimum for max results. Preferably 3 sessions a week. Keep your HR within the Zone 2 range steady through out the duration. Keep increasing your wattage as you progress. Here’s my for reference purpose https://t.co/LiiPXTFBTG

name: Sandeep Mall
text: So you will need some machinery help to stay in Zone 2 continuously for the time. If u are athletically very fit you can run. Kipchoge when he ran the WR marathon in 2 hours had lactate level below 2 for through out except last 15 minutes. These are exceptional athletes.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: To do Zone 2 exercise you need a machine which produce the same output. The best is a Bicycle. Indoor Bicycle. You can also walk on treadmill with some elevation. Most people will not cross Zone 1 while walking. And will cross Zone 2 if they start jogging.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: The science behind this is fascinating but too long a subject for a twitter thread. U may like to read more about ATP generation, Krebs cycle etc. Khan Academy has some good videos on the chemical reactions happening but just know best place to lose fat is zone 2.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: My RHR is 50. Calculate your reserve HR which will be MHR - RHR. So for me 165 - 50 = 115. My Zone 2 will be 50-75% of Heart rate reserve ie. 58 to 81(rounding off) plus RHR which is 50. So range becomes 108 to 131 bpm. This is where Fat burning happens.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: The easiest way to know your zone 2 range is first calculate your max Heart rate. MHR is approx 220- ur age. So for me its 220-55 = 165. Know your resting heart rate. If you have a smart watch u will know or else just count your pulse every morning for ten days and do an average.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: But doing a little strenuous workout you are going to start making lactate. Even the best athlete in the world will. The fitter the person is the more work they can do with less lactate. Zone 2 is the level where you can understand how metabolically fit you are

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Explaining today Zone -2. Zone 2 is defined as the highest metabolic output/work that you can sustain while keeping hour lactate level below 2 mmol/L. A healthy person when at rest has a lactate level of 1.0 mmol/L. Usually doing your daily chores should not increase this.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Most of us who exercise want to lose fat. Doing this long thread on what & how u can . Your weekend read. My framework for exercise has four components - strength, stability, aerobic efficiency and anaerobic performance. Heres my last 12 weeks workout data. https://t.co/FZdalAQQ86

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
..Breathe right. Stay calm. You don’t have to react to anything as it never solves the problem. Stress plays the most destructive role in your life 
5. Managing drugs, hormones and supplements. Get regular check ups done and supplement right. Check what molecules u r putting in

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
1. Nutrition - Eat protein and vegetables in every meal. Avoid sugar. 
2. Exercise - At least 200-300 mins a week. Mix of strength, cardio and mobility 
3. Sleep - 8 hours of sleep with at least 2 hours of deep sleep. 
4. Stress management - Spend mindful minutes. Meditate...

name: Sandeep Mall
text: While death is inevitable, the three points of health span are not. You can easily manage them. It’s in your own hand and not very complicated as most marketing and SM influencers make it out. It all depends on prioritising these five things. Make them your life goals

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
1) Physical decline - decline in mobility, muscles, strength, aerobic functions, movement, sexual function, freedom from pain
2) Cognitive decline - decline in memory, processing speed
3) Emotional decline - decline in sense of purpose, mindfulness, social support

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Longevity is a balance of lifespan ( living longer) and health span ( living better). 80% of non smoking population die because of heart attack, stroke, cancer and accidental death. Health span is decline of three main things

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Heres a set of Strength training and mobility mix which can be done at home covering basic body movements. Keep loading them as you progress. 3-4 sets each exercise 8-15 reps. https://t.co/zXmxjY3ckE

name: Sandeep Mall
text: I don't recommend Cardio mixed up with strength training. Keep them separate. And Warm up with Dynamic stretching and cool down. Rest. Eat enough protein. If you can afford get a trainer. Wrong posture will harm you tremendously.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: To properly breathe during strength training inhale on the eccentric phase and exhale during the concentric phase. Exhale while you're doing the hardest work, and inhale as you're coming back to your starting position.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: How to breathe - By closing the mouth and breathing entirely through the nose, your muscles will receive approx 20% more oxygen. This will help faster recovery between sets. Means you can lift more and gain more.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: What to eat pre, post and during workout? Before a workout you need energy, during a workout you need hydration and after workout you need repair. Eat 90 mins before a workout .During workout sip enough water. Post workout take protein rich diet. Your body needs protein to repair

name: Sandeep Mall
text: How much rest between sets? First need to know why rest? Its not for muscle recovery. Its to stabilize your cardio vascular system. To bring the heart rate down. Keep your HR between 45- 80% of your MHR.

name: Sandeep Mall
text:
..but that’s not effective as your load is less 8*6 + 8*6 + 8*6 = 144. SO to load higher we need to exceed the total of 150.
Grip the bar or DB deep in your palm, close to the heel of the hand.Squeeze as hard as you can to get those individual finger flexors fully firing.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Now how to define load. Load is basically No of reps X weight. So if you are doing some workout – 3 sets of 10 reps each with 5 kgs then your load is 10*5 + 10*5 + 10*5 = 150. Next time when you do if you do 3 sets of 8 reps with 6 Kgs, you will feel I have increased weight..

name: Sandeep Mall
text: ...more week after week, your body's physiology will be forced to change. Higher Reps or more weights? Its about volume. The first condition to be satisfied , to get any output, is muscle fiber rapture. Which happens when you load the muscles to a higher degree than last time.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Repeat your workout for four consecutive weeks. 4 weeks works well. It’s a good sweet spot from a physiological standpoint and a mental one too.Your body is stubborn and does not want to change. By keeping your workouts consistent and challenging yourself just a little....

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Recommended training split: full body workouts 3 times per week.This allows you to hit the same muscles 3 times per week.This frequency is necessary to maximise the growth stimulus and also enhances technique learning to be exposed to similar movement patterns more frequently

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Weight selection - stick to ‘moderate effort’ in the first 8-12 weeks of training. This is in part to prevent excessive soreness and to ensure proper form. At this stage in a person's training journey, technique practice is the primary goal.

name: Sandeep Mall
text: Know your MHR. The best formula is 211 – 0.64* age. MHR is max hear rate beyond which you red-line your heart. Don’t cross that.Don’t pick up your phone. Don’t gossip in between your sets. Don’t let your heart rate fall below 50% MHR ( which means you are taking too much rest).
